Subject: Re: [T2] rough or no idle, poor performance with warm ambient

On Wednesday, April 05, 2006, at 05:19PM, David Parisi <vwwesty(-at-)sbcglobal.net> wrote:

>Have a 2.0L motor, w/ 1.8L heads, solids lifters, and 100 cam built  
>by AVP.  Ever since installed 2 yrs, 5000 miles ago, the motor has  
>dismal fuel mileage (12 mpg).

Not uncommon from those budget rebuilds.

>Did a compression test and all cylinders are between 100 to 105 psi.   
>Checked valve clearance and all are within spec.  Compression seems a  
>little low for fresh motor w/ 5000 miles.

Do a leakdown test. I bet you'll have a lot of leakage from the valves even though the clearance is ok. Heads are a weakness on those motors while everything else seems to be properly assembled.

>I am lost, and ready to  
>throw in a SVDA dizzy.  But I don't think its the problem.

That wouldn't hurt. You should be running that distributor on any stock motor.

